•	verify that models were registered correctly 
•	test data entry without custom views 
•	confirm relationships were working 
•	inspect data in a structured way 

What I configured
I registered the core models:
•	Community 
•	Dwelling 
•	Tenant 
•	RepairRequest 
•	MaintenanceUpdate 
I also improved usability by using:
•	list_display 
•	search_fields 
•	list_filter 

Why this improved the project
These admin improvements helped in two ways:
1.	they made manual testing easier 
2.	they made the backend more professional and maintainable 
For example:
•	search fields allow quick lookup of records 
•	list filters support category/status-based browsing 
•	list display shows important columns clearly 

Thought process
I saw admin.py as both a testing tool and a management interface. It was especially valuable during early development because it allowed the team to work with real data before all user-facing pages were complete.


